      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you, and i appreciate the warning. it's just that i'm really struggling to function right now with my studies and it feels like the sertraline is just plateauing. if i was to just take a very small amount of the St. Johns Wort, maybe like once every few days or just a tiny dose, would that bypass the risk? i just want something natural to help me through finals without having to go through the whole process of changing my actual prescription.",
